(secondQuint)Study of External Beam Radiation Therapy With and Without Hormonal Therapy to Treat Prostate Cancer.

 This was a randomized study comparing external beam radiation therapy with total androgen ablation for 6 months with radiation therapy alone.

 Drugs were given 2 months prior, 2 months during, and 2 months after radiation therapy.

 Eulexin and Lupron or Zoladex was used in this study.

